      "comment_id" : 77770495,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The language used in the LinkedList column of this table is contradictory. Both prepending and appending to a LinkedList are faster than adding elements in the middle, but slower than prepending or appending to ArrayLists or Vectors. This is because every insertion requires memory allocation with non-local references, increasing the chance of cache misses. Even though lookup in a LinkedList is linear with the number of elements and a pointer to the end isn&#39;t stored, appending is still faster than prepending because memory is only reallocated for one element."
